          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "All Medicare recipients pay premiums for outpatient care, which is called Medicare Part B. That money can be funneled into traditional government Medicare plans, or into Medicare Advantage plans run by private insurers that are incentivized to limit the amount of care that elders receive.",
